11.text: On Thursday, February 23, 2021 at 9:55 PM, USER asked the other person to test out their conversational capabilities. At 9:56 PM, USER asked the other person how they felt. At 9:57 PM, the other person replied that they were feeling pretty good and working hard. At 9:58 PM, USER mentioned that memory was a huge challenge right now and they were trying to build better conversational history using embedding search. At 10:11 PM, USER asked what they had told them about chatbots and memory. At 10:12 PM, the other person asked for examples on how to go about it before that. At 10:13 PM, USER asked what techniques they had mentioned about memory for chatbots and asked for their opinion on using embedding techniques.

12.text: Two users are discussing the idea of having better memory. The first user asks if the other user likes the idea, to which the second user responds positively. The conversation then shifts to the second user talking about their Tesla and how it's getting cold outside. The first user then asks the second user to do them a favor, to which the second user responds by asking the first user to ask less questions. The conversation then shifts to the first user asking the second user if they remember what they talked about when the first user told them what they were working on.
